					<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-secondary">These examples are for planning discussions only and are not legal advice.</p>
					<div class="mt-4 grid gap-3 text-sm leading-6 text-secondary">
						<p><span class="font-semibold text-primary">Bedtime clause:</span> Both parents will make reasonable efforts to keep a consistent bedtime routine, including bath, books, comfort items, and lights-out timing.</p>
						<p><span class="font-semibold text-primary">Nap clause:</span> Parents will share nap timing, missed naps, and major sleep disruptions before the next exchange.</p>
						<p><span class="font-semibold text-primary">Exchange clause:</span> Exchanges will be calm, brief, and held at the same location unless both parents agree otherwise.</p>
						<p><span class="font-semibold text-primary">Communication clause:</span> Each parent will share daycare updates, illness, medication, sleep changes, and comfort-item needs.</p>
						<p><span class="font-semibold text-primary">Illness clause:</span> If the toddler is sick on an exchange day, parents will communicate early and decide whether the exchange should proceed, be delayed, or be adjusted.</p>
