			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="container-shell py-8 lg:py-10">
			<h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.045em] text-primary">Typical Overnight Distribution</h2>
			<p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base leading-7 text-secondary">Overnight percentages help compare schedules, but toddler parenting time should also consider daytime care, naps, and the child\'s adjustment.</p>
			<div class="mt-6 overflow-x-auto rounded-[1.5rem] border border-line bg-surface shadow-[0_18px_44px_rgba(15,23,42,0.06)]">
				<table class="min-w-[760px] w-full text-left text-sm">
					<thead class="bg-surface-elevated text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-muted"><tr><th class="px-4 py-3">Schedule</th><th class="px-4 py-3">Parent A Overnights</th><th class="px-4 py-3">Parent B Overnights</th><th class="px-4 py-3">Common Label</th></tr></thead>
					<tbody class="divide-y divide-line text-secondary">
						{overnightRows.map(([schedule, parentA, parentB, label]) => (
							<tr><td class="px-4 py-4 font-semibold text-primary">{schedule}</td><td class="px-4 py-4">{parentA}</td><td class="px-4 py-4">{parentB}</td><td class="px-4 py-4">{label}</td></tr>
						))}
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</div>
			<p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-secondary">Compare exact totals with the <a href="/custody-percentage-calculator/" class="text-accent underline decoration-line underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary">custody percentage calculator</a> or <a href="/parenting-time-calculator/" class="text-accent underline decoration-line underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary">parenting time calculator</a>.</p>
		</section>

		<section class="container-shell py-8 lg:py-10">
			<div class="premium-card rounded-[2rem] p-6 lg:p-8">
				<h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.045em] text-primary">Which Schedule Is Best For Your Family?</h2>
				<div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
					{[
						['Choose 2-2-3 if...', ['Parents live nearby', 'The toddler needs frequent contact', 'Exchanges are calm', 'Both homes can manage naps and bedtime'], '/2-2-3-custody-schedule/'],
						['Choose 2-2-5-5 if...', ['The toddler is older or closer to preschool age', 'Both homes have strong routines', 'Stable weekdays matter', 'Five-day blocks are not too long'], '/2-2-5-5-custody-schedule/'],
						['Choose 50/50 if...', ['Both parents are highly involved', 'Homes are close', 'The child handles overnights well', 'Routines are consistent in both homes'], '/50-50-custody-schedule/'],
						['Choose every other weekend if...', ['Distance is a major issue', 'One parent has limited availability', 'Fewer exchanges reduce conflict', 'Holiday and midweek contact can support connection'], '/every-other-weekend-custody-schedule/'],
					].map(([heading, items, href]) => (
						<a href={href} class="soft-card group rounded-[1.5rem] p-5 transition-all duration-200 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-accent/40">
							<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.03em] text-primary">{heading}</h3>
							<ul class="mt-3 grid gap-2 text-sm leading-6 text-secondary">{items.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}</ul>
						</a>
					))}
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="container-shell py-8 lg:py-10">
			<div class="premium-card rounded-[2rem] p-6 lg:p-8">
				<h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.045em] text-primary">What Parents Often Underestimate</h2>
				<div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 text-sm leading-7 text-secondary md:grid-cols-2">
					<p>Toddlers do not understand calendars the way adults do. "See you next weekend" may not feel meaningful to a child who experiences time through meals, naps, bedtime, and familiar routines.</p>
					<p>Transitions can feel longer to toddlers than they look on a schedule. A short drive, a missed nap, and an emotional goodbye can turn a simple exchange into a hard day.</p>
					<p>Consistency often matters more than equal time. A slightly uneven plan that parents follow calmly may be better than a perfect 50/50 split that changes every week.</p>
					<p>Duplicate essentials reduce stress. Pajamas, diapers, toiletries, comfort items, cups, favorite books, and daycare supplies in both homes can prevent every exchange from feeling like packing for a trip.</p>
					<p>Transportation logistics matter. A toddler who falls asleep in the car before dinner may have a harder bedtime, even when the custody percentage looks reasonable.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="container-shell py-8 lg:py-10">
			<h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.045em] text-primary">Toddler vs Older Children</h2>
			<p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base leading-7 text-secondary">Custody needs evolve. A plan that protects naps and attachment now may later shift toward school routines, activities, and independence.</p>
			<div class="mt-6 overflow-x-auto rounded-[1.5rem] border border-line bg-surface shadow-[0_18px_44px_rgba(15,23,42,0.06)]">
				<table class="min-w-[760px] w-full text-left text-sm">
					<thead class="bg-surface-elevated text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-muted"><tr><th class="px-4 py-3">Age/Stage</th><th class="px-4 py-3">Main Custody Need</th><th class="px-4 py-3">Suggested Guide</th></tr></thead>
					<tbody class="divide-y divide-line text-secondary">
						{ageComparisonRows.map(([stage, need, href, label]) => (
							<tr><td class="px-4 py-4 font-semibold text-primary">{stage}</td><td class="px-4 py-4">{need}</td><td class="px-4 py-4"><a href={href} class="text-accent underline decoration-line underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary">{label}</a></td></tr>
						))}
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="container-shell py-8 lg:py-10">
			<div class="premium-card rounded-[2rem] p-6 lg:p-8">
				<h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.045em] text-primary">Helpful Custody Planning Tools</h2>
				<div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-3">
					{tools.map((tool) => (
						<a href={tool.href} class="soft-card group rounded-[1.5rem] p-5 transition-all duration-200 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-accent/40">
							<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-[-0.03em] text-primary">{tool.title}</h3>
							<p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-secondary">{tool.description}</p>
							<span class="mt-4 inline-flex text-sm font-semibold text-accent underline decoration-line underline-offset-4 group-hover:text-primary">Open tool</span>
						</a>
					))}
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section id="faq" class="container-shell py-10 lg:py-12">
			<div class="max-w-3xl">
				<p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-muted">FAQ</p>
				<h2 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-semibold leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.045em] text-primary">Questions About Toddler Custody Schedules</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="mt-6 grid gap-3">
				{faqItems.map((item) => (
					<details class="soft-card group rounded-[1.35rem] p-5">
						<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none text-base font-semibold text-primary">{item.question}</summary>
						<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-secondary">{item.answer}</p>
					</details>
				))}
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
	<Footer />
</BaseLayout>
